CASTING CALL ‚Äì BATH

We‚Äôre looking for two actors for a 1600s period-drama music video filming in Bath. 
This is an unpaid collaborative project and we‚Äôre aiming for atmospheric, experimental, vintage-horror-style performances.

‚∏ª

FEMALE ACTOR (18‚Äì30) ‚Äì ‚ÄúAgnes‚Äù

A farmer‚Äôs daughter with a wide emotional range, from love to rage.
‚Ä¢ Experimental physical performance (no audio recorded)
‚Ä¢ Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
‚Ä¢ White/European descent
‚Ä¢ Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

‚∏ª

MALE ACTOR (18‚Äì35)

A wealthy, confident, and devious character who tries to charm Agnes. Includes a scene where he becomes possessed and shifts into a zombie-like state.
‚Ä¢ Strong physical storytelling (no audio recorded)
‚Ä¢ Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
‚Ä¢ Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

‚∏ª

If you fit either brief and are interested, please email coleoakley101@gmail.com to apply with the required materials.

Thank you.

items.text:
Free Showreel Offer

Full booked for now. But I'll definitely be doing this again so if you're interested follow Lizzie.LuluProductions   for more opportunities. Thanks everyone! x

Hi everyone!

I've been volunteering in the filmmaking world for about a year now, and I still have a lot to learn. I'm currently offering free showreels to actors based in Yorkshire as a way to build up my camera operating and directing portfolio.

I‚Äôve written lots of new scripts, and I'm planning another showreel day on either the 28th, the 30th of December, or the 2nd of January.

Each showreel will take around 45 minutes to film. I'm happy to pair people up, but if you'd prefer to arrange your own scene partner, that‚Äôs absolutely fine too!

If you're interested, please message me or email lizzieluluproductions@gmail.com ‚Äî I‚Äôd love to hear from you! Please only email if you are interested as I have lots of people emailing but then ignoring me when they receive their call times.

Many thanks. x

message.text:
David Reynolds returns for one reason.
To jump.

Years of military PTSD and childhood trauma have followed him home.
His battles are no longer fought outside.
They live in his head.
And no matter where he runs, there is no escape.

The bridge stands waiting.
Cold. Hard. Steel.
Resilient, yet weakened every time someone walks across it.
A mirror of the man standing before it.

David comes back broken.
Ready to end it.

Then he learns the truth.
He has a son.

For a moment, hope breaks through.

It does not last.

Grief and fury collide.
David turns outward, cleaning up the mess around him.
But his greatest enemy was never out there.

It was always himself.

David Reynolds.
And he will not go gentle.

**HORT FILM CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDIGENOUS FEMALE ACTOR**

**Project Type:** Independent Short Film
**Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Dates:** March, 2026
**ROLE**
* **Indigenous / First Nations / M√©tis / Inuit female actor**
* **Age range:** approx. 18‚Äì25
* Acting experience preferred but not required
**CHARACTER**
* A quiet, observant young woman navigating a moment of personal change.
**REQUIREMENTS**
* Must self-identify as Indigenous
* Based in Vancouver or able to work locally
* Comfortable working on an independent short film set
**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)
* (Optional) Demo reel or self-tape

**Submit to:** hiayj23@gmail.com

Maggie Wallace

items.text:
In case you missed it‚Ä¶.

A special shout-out to Red Leg Brewing Company for being an absolutely amazing venue!

Get Ready, Denver!

The momentum continues! We are thrilled to announce we're heading to the Mile High City. We will be revealing the location and details for our Denver Networking Event happening in January very soon!

Follow us so you don't miss the announcement!

www.kickassfilmfest.com

sharedPost.text:
What an incredible night! A massive thank you to every filmmaker and creative who attended our Colorado Springs Meet-N-Greet on December 6th. The energy was electric, and the connections forged were exactly what these events are for: uniting newbies, veterans, and everyone in between for networking and potential new collaborators!

A special shout-out to Red Leg Brewing Company for being an absolutely amazing venue!

Get Ready, Denver!

The momentum continues! We are thrilled to announce we're heading to the Mile High City. We will be revealing the location and details for our Denver Networking Event happening in January very soon!

Follow us so you don't miss the announcement!

www.kickassfilmfest.com

#filmmaking #Networking #coloradosprings #denver #creativecommunity #kickassfilmfest #coloradofilm #filmproduction #filmmakerslife #filmcrew #Filmmakers

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

‚≠ê OFFICIAL CASTING CALL 

Building a Core Acting Team for a New Film/Stage Universe

I‚Äôm assembling a core long-term team (like Kevin Hart‚Äôs Plastic Cup Boyz / Adam Sandler‚Äôs crew) to develop a new film universe plus multiple original projects.

Phase 1:
A small stage adaptation of my book (just to get everyone in sync).

Phase 2:
We turn that story into our first feature film.

Phase 3 and beyond:
Continuous films inside the Frenchie Extended Universe + original projects outside the universe.
Everyone on the core team will be acting, producing, writing, and helping shape future projects together.

Roles Currently Casting (Core Team Only):

Riley (F) ‚Äì Love interest of the main character. Loyal, grounded, warm energy.

Isabella (F, Puerto Rican) ‚Äì Fierce, supportive, emotional backbone of the group.

Crumbs (M) ‚Äì Comedic timing, lovable troublemaker.

Jordan (M) ‚Äì Serious, loyal, big heart but stern presence.

Marcus (M, Black) ‚Äì Later-series antagonist; charismatic, powerful, intimidating.

Jimmy/Frenchie (M) ‚Äì Already cast.

What I need from you:

Send me a 30‚Äì45 second video reading a short line for the character you‚Äôre interested in.
Nothing fancy ‚Äî I just need to see presence, expression, and vibe.

What this is NOT:

This is NOT a one-off gig or a ‚Äúshow up, get paid, leave‚Äù job.
This is a long-term creative family building something from scratch together.

What this IS:

‚úî A team
‚úî A pipeline
‚úî A chance to grow into acting/producing/directing
‚úî Multiple projects ahead
‚úî Long-term involvement as the universe expands

If you‚Äôre hungry, reliable, and want to build something real ‚Äî comment INTERESTED and I‚Äôll DM you a line to read.

Let‚Äôs build something Buffalo can be proud of. üî•
‚Äî Jimmy

items.text:
**Casting Certified Fitness, Yoga & Pilates Trainers**
**PAID OPPORTUNITY**

Hello everyone!
I‚Äôm currently looking for **certified trainers** for an upcoming project with **a major activewear brand**. We are preparing a new series of social-media training videos and are now conducting a **preliminary casting**.

We‚Äôre looking for:
‚Ä¢ Fitness / functional training coaches
‚Ä¢ Yoga instructors
‚Ä¢ Pilates instructors
‚Ä¢ Stretching / mobility specialists

We welcome trainers of **different ages and backgrounds**, as long as you are certified, experienced, and confident working with beginner-level clients.

The project includes participation in **on-camera training shoots**.
Details regarding filming dates and compensation will be discussed individually with selected candidates.

If you:
‚Ä¢ hold valid certifications
‚Ä¢ have at least 5 years of teaching experience
‚Ä¢ have on-camera experience (a plus, but not required)
‚Ä¢ are open to collaboration

‚Äî please feel free to **DM me directly**.
When reaching out, include your training specialty and a link to your social media or examples of your teaching.

Looking forward to connecting with talented professionals!

Hi! We are LOOKING FOR A MALE ACTOR for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2026 in the H≈±v√∂sv√∂lgy area.

The title for the film is KITART√ÅS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. The role requires fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

The short film will be submitted to local and international film festivalsüé¨

This is a low-budget short film, but it will have a symbolic paymentüí∞

We are looking for a person to play one of the lead roles.

√ÅD√ÅM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under Istv√°n‚Äôs command. √Åd√°m is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25‚Äì30 years old.

1.75cm - 1.80cm 

Fit or in a healthy weight

Strong presence

Must speak English and Hungarian fluently

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

‚úâÔ∏è contactingdianag@gmail.com

Deadline: 31/12/2025

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

Most auditions don‚Äôt fail because of acting ‚Äî they fail because casting never reaches the performance. Friction in self-tapes like poor lighting, distracting audio, or unstable framing pulls attention away before your work even lands.

MyAuditionAI.com is an advanced self-tape app and AI audition partner built to eliminate that friction. Get instant coaching and actionable feedback on lighting, sound, camera presence, and performance ‚Äî all before casting ever sees your tape.

This audition preparation app includes powerful AI acting assistant features like self-tape coaching tools, a scene analysis tool for actors, script rehearsal tools, and cold read rehearsal apps to help you stay ready under pressure.

üëâ Try www.MyAuditionAI.com free for 7 days and start recording auditions at home with confidence. Submit self-tapes that are clear, professional, and effortless to watch.

sharedPost.text:
Casting-Aufruf: üé•üé¨

f√ºr unseren Kurzfilm "G√ºterbahnhof 23" suchen wir noch eine m√§nnliche Nebenrolle und Komparsen in M√ºnchen. Die ersten Szenen sind bereits abgedreht. Das Casting findet online statt. 

Was wird genau gesucht? 

Ein Sicherheitsbeamten als Kollege f√ºr die Rolle Frau Steinmetz. ( Nebenrolle ) 

Spielalter: 45-60 Jahre. Leichte Strenge. Muss etwas Druck aus√ºben k√∂nnen. 

Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft k√∂nnen leider von uns nicht √ºbernommen werden, daher sind Darsteller aus M√ºnchen und Umgebung super. Gerne auch aus anderen Bundesl√§ndern, wenn die Reise selbst √ºbernommen werden k√∂nnte.

Das ist unser erstes selbstgedrehtes Projekt, weshalb wir die Kosten ( noch ) nicht √ºbernehmen k√∂nnen. 

Die Castings finden ab dem 05. Januar 2026 statt. 

Ihr k√∂nnt euch aber gerne jetzt schon ein Castingtermin sichern. 

Es ist ein No-Budget-Projekt. F√ºr Verpflegung ist aber gesorgt. 

Viele Gr√º√üe, und viel Erfolg beim Casting! üé•üé¨

------------------

Casting Call: üé•üé¨

For our short film "G√ºterbahnhof 23" (Freight Depot 23), we are looking for a male supporting actor and extras in Munich. The first scenes have already been filmed. The casting call will be online.

What exactly are we looking for?

A security guard to play a colleague for the character of Ms. Steinmetz. (Supporting role)

Playing age: 45-60 years. Slightly strict. Must be able to exert some pressure.

Unfortunately, we cannot cover travel and accommodation costs, so actors from Munich and the surrounding area are ideal. We are also open to actors from other German states if they can cover their own travel expenses.

This is our first self-produced project, which is why we cannot (yet) cover these costs.

The castings will take place starting January 5, 2026.

However, you are welcome to reserve a casting appointment now.

This is a no-budget project. Food and drinks will be provided.

Best wishes, and good luck with the casting! üé•üé¨

items.text:
12/12/25

(This Is My) Family (Short Film)

A Comedy about family dynamics

A family near breaking point, implodes in one night. 

Shooting April location TBC

Auditioning: We want to receive self tapes first and those who make it to the next stage, we would love in person auditions by late January of 2026. 

Travel Expenses paid

Student film being screened at The BFI and will be entered into film festivals

Elizabeth (50s-60s) - Narcissistic mother who dominates her kids' lives. She speaks her mind much to the reluctance of everyone around her..

Marie (30s-40s) - She‚Äôs in the middle of a mid-life crisis and she blames elizabeth as she thinks she‚Äôs not the perfect mother that she presents herself as. So Marie rebels against this supposed ‚Äòperfect family‚Äô.

Shaun (30-40s) - Shaun simply accepts his place in the world and has very little self respect. He is in a loveless relationship with his wife (Claire) however he does not rebel against her out of fear of living life alone in his 40s. Yet again every man has his breaking point. 

Clare (30s-40s) - Clare needs power and control, so she has found a man she can excerpt this power on (Shaun.) Clare and Elizabeth are very similar and therefore team up to inflate each other's egos at the expense of Marie and Shaun. 

Email: tylerbrownework@gmail.com for further details

Please only respond if you are based in England as our budget will not cover travel from abroad.

items.text:
We are casting confident, expressive individuals to appear as contestants/guests on a high-energy, unscripted talk show inspired by classic formats such as Jeremy Kyle and Jerry Springer.

The show will be hosted by massive influencer, who will take the role of the presenter, guiding conversations, mediating disputes, and attempting to resolve real or semi-scripted personal conflicts in an entertaining, fast-paced environment.

This is a performance-based role requiring strong personality, emotional range, and the ability to react naturally on camera.

Role Description ‚Äì Contestants / Guests

Selected participants will appear on the show as individuals involved in a personal conflict, relationship issue, family dispute, secret reveal, or moral dilemma. Scenarios may include (but are not limited to):

Relationship breakdowns or accusations

Love triangles or cheating allegations

Friendship or family fallouts

Hidden secrets or confrontations

Lifestyle or behavioural conflicts

You will be expected to:

Play a character or heightened version of yourself

Engage in open, confrontational, or emotionally charged discussions

React naturally to questions, accusations, and audience/chat interaction

Remain in character throughout the segment

Be comfortable with raised voices, dramatic moments, and comedic tension

Ideal Candidate

Aged 18+

Confident and expressive on camera

Comfortable with confrontation and emotional performance

Strong improvisation skills (acting experience is a plus, but not required)

Able to think quickly and respond naturally in live situations

Thick-skinned and comfortable being part of viral, high-reach content

Important Notes

This is entertainment content, not a real counselling or therapy show

Scenarios may be planned, semi-scripted, or improvised

Content will be broadcast live and clipped for social platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.)

Applicants must consent to being filmed and distributed online

Compensation

Paid role

Rate dependent on role complexity, screen time, and experience

topComments.text: Looking for uneducated thickos with anger problems. Got it.
People who wash their dirty linen in public for cash .  Have we not grown out of these shows .

CASTING/CREW CALL ‚Äì NEW DOCUMENTARY (Los Angeles, Jan/Feb 2026) 
ÔøΩFrom a TV Producer with Discovery & History Channel credits. 

I‚Äôm currently casting for a new documentary that explores the powerful stories we attach to the objects we treasure most. I‚Äôm looking for people who have one meaningful item something that, when held, brings back emotion, memory, or a story that shaped who you are.

Your object could be:
* A family heirloom
* A gift from someone who has passed
* A reminder of a relationship or life-changing moment
* Or simply something that holds deep, personal significance

This project will highlight everyday people and the extraordinary stories behind the things they hold dear.

FILMING:ÔøΩLos Angeles ‚Äî January & February 2026
If you have an item that carries emotional weight and a story you're willing to share on camera, I‚Äôd love to hear from you.

TO APPLY:ÔøΩPlease get in touch and share a brief description of yourself, your item, and the story behind it. Photos welcome but not required.
Looking forward to hearing your story.

EMAIL: breynolsbri@gmail.com
INSTAGRAM: @bryannareynolds

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT FINAL FILM üé¨

**PAID** Hi everyone! We are currently casting for WISP, a haunting coming-of-age drama about isolation, queer longing, and the grip of an unseen presence.

To be Shot in: West Yorkshire.

 

Synopsis:

Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam turns up on New Year‚Äôs Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he‚Äôs long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

 

Characters:

NOAH (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Quiet, introspective, emotionally guarded. Must be able to convey internal conflict, subtle fear, and vulnerability with restraint.

SAM (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah‚Äôs best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

 

Shooting: 12/2 ‚Äì 15/2   (Night Shoots)

Payment: TBD ‚Äî we are happy to discuss this with you.          

 

üì© Contact: [jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com](mailto:jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com) with Showreel if available. Script will be available.

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested.  üå≥üñ§

items.text:
## **üé≠ Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

items.text:
I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

items.text:
Hey!

Wir produzieren f√ºr die lokalen For-Future-Gruppen der Region T√ºbingen satirische Beitr√§ge, die an "Die Anstalt" (ZDF) angelehnt sind und haben deswegen noch einige Rollen zu besetzen.

Kurzum versucht Mutter Natur in einem fiktiven Gerichtsraum gegen Friedrich Merz das Recht zu erstreiten, endlich als juristische Person wahrgenommen zu werden. Dabei helfen ihr Zeugen wie "Die Psyche der Menschen", "Der Vorgarten" und "Der Begradigte Fluss". items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

items.text:
STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING 

Shooting dates: 23rd-25th January

Location: Vancouver, North Vancouver

Volunteer, lunch and copy of film provided. 

**MARTY (20-25)**
* A young pianist struggling with anxiety and health issues. His passion for music is strong, but he is haunted by self-doubt and physical limitations. Emotionally vulnerable, he carries the weight of the past, yet despite the toll on his body and mind, he persists in pursuing his dreams.

**MARTY'S MOTHER (40s-50s)**
* A supportive, hard-working single mother. Cares deeply for her son and masks her worries about his skill with a calm, composed demeanor, despite the mental and physical toll it‚Äôs taking on her.

**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to an audition, January 7th. If unavailable, a self-tape will be accepted. 

**Submit to:** melodymovie2026@gmail.com

Dieses Erkl√§rvideo (KI generiert) ist ein Auszug, vielleicht eher eine verk√ºrzte Zusammenfassung, des Buches "HAGIA SOFIA, Siehst Du noch den Wei√üen Turm", und enth√§lt sowohl narrative Kapitel als auch umfangreiche Quellenangaben und formale Abschnitte. Die fiktive Haupthandlung dreht sich um eine Gruppe von Protagonisten, darunter die Historiker 

Elias und Nikos sowie Geheimdienstagenten, die versuchen, einen 

verheerenden Terroranschlag des sogenannten "Schattenkonvents" auf die Hagia Sofia in Thessaloniki zu verhindern, wobei die "Sonne von Vergina" als Code-Botschaft dient. Parallel zur Thriller-Erz√§hlung √ºber Verfolgungsjagden und das Entschl√ºsseln von Hinweisen im Wei√üen Turm und in Katakomben werden detaillierte geopolitische und strategische Hintergr√ºnde

 pr√§sentiert, die Thessalonikis Rolle als zentraler Verkehrsknotenpunkt 

und Energie-Hub sowie die tief verwurzelten Spannungen zwischen 

Griechenland, der T√ºrkei und anderen regionalen Akteuren hervorheben. 

Die umfangreichen Quellenverweise belegen die historischen, geografischen und milit√§rischen Fakten, die als Basis f√ºr die fiktive Geschichte √ºber False Flag Operationen und die Destabilisierung der Region dienen.

Hi everyone!

We are running casting calls for an automotive accessories brand. Below is the casting call:

Casting for a warm and comedic commercial following a worn-down ‚Äúpersonified car seat‚Äù who rediscovers confidence, comfort, and joy after getting a fresh start with Coverland seat covers.

Please email jieying.w@coverland.com with casting profiles, headshots and reels for audition details. 

**Production Dates:** 2-Day Production between (Jan 16-18, 2026)

**Location: **Los Angeles & Orange County, CA

**Union Status:** Non-Union

**Requesting Submissions From: **LA Locals Only

**Roles Casting:**
* **Jerry Seatman**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $400/Day, (est. 2 days of work)

**Role Description:**

Male, 43‚Äì55, A middle-aged man who also happens to be a literal human-car-seat hybrid. 

Mostly facial acting, we are looking for someone to portray a middle-aged, defeated, working family man then having his major transformation. Think used car salesman, or insurance salesman. 

Notes: Actors should be comfortable with light physical comedy and playing sincerity within an absurd premise. Prosthetics / costume elements may be involved to emulate the human-car-seat look.

* **Nancy**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $400/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Female, 36-46, Warm, observant, and quietly supportive. She sees Jerry‚Äôs insecurities before he says them out loud and ultimately gives him the gift that changes everything. This role requires emotional subtlety and natural warmth.

* **Daughter**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $300/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Female, 9-14, Bright, affectionate, and playful. Natural, expressive, comfortable on camera.

* **Son**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $300/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Male, 9-14, Energetic and joyful. Looking for natural, playful energy.

items.text:
Genre: Dark fantasy / Psychological Horror

Length: 25 - 30 minutes

Location: BERLIN 

Shooting: End of January/ Beginning of February

Budget: unpaid (graduation film)

Hey everyone, we are casting several supporting roles for a dark atmospheric graduation proof-of-concept film that blends mythology, psychological horror, and realism. This project explores power, identity, and the uncanny hidden beneath everyday life.

If you‚Äôre a fan of The Sandman, Pan‚Äôs Labrynth, and Only Lovers Left Alive, then you will feel right at home.

Actors of all backgrounds are encouraged to apply.

ROLES AVAILABLE

Spati owner (30s - 60s) - Male

A grounded ordinary presence in the mortal world. Calm and slightly detached. The Spati owner acts as an anchor to reality before things begin to unravel.

Ria (20s - 30s) - Female

Sharp, perceptive, emotionally guarded. She carries tension beneath casual conversation.

Pierre (20s - 30s) - Male

Charming on the surface but unsettling underneath. He speaks easily but holds something back.

Darius (20s - 30s) - Male

Charismatic, confident, slightly arrogant. Darius is a natural leader in social spaces. However, under pressure, his warmth slips.

Coveliat (30s) - Female

A creature of death. Uncanny, ritualistic presence, more felt than understood. Her claws can slash through the strongest of materials.

Girl 1 (20s) - Female

Social, warm, slightly obvious. She represents normality and comfort, until that comfort curdles into unease.

Girl 2 (20s -30s) - Female

More observant than girl 1. She picks up on subtle shifts in tone and energy. Friendly, but with flickers of suspicion.

IF INTERESTED

We would kindly ask you to send an email to:

celia.t@catalyst-students.com

The submission will be done in the form of self-tapes rather than in-person auditions.

The self-tape information will be sent via email.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.
